title: Ceiling Medallion, 1875–1906
creditline: Museum purchase from Smithsonian Institution Collections Acquisition Program and Sarah Cooper-Hewitt Funds
description: Large anglo-Japanesque ceiling medallion in fan shape, with the main focus having the appearance of a folded wallpaper border, containing many red roses. A fleur-de-lis is at the one corner.  Contains illustration showing application for use as a border corner or a medallion.

tombstone.epitaph:
Ceiling Medallion, 1875–1906.
1875–1906. Block-printed. Museum purchase from Smithsonian Institution Collections Acquisition Program and Sarah Cooper-Hewitt Funds. 1995-165-16.
